feat(display-tablets): add real-time config updates via Server-Sent Events

Implement SSE-based push notifications to instantly refresh tablets when configuration changes.

When a user updates a tablet's configuration via PUT, the tablet is now instantly notified through a persistent SSE connection, eliminating the need for polling or manual refresh.

Architecture:
- TabletConfigNotifier service: Manages SSE connections and broadcasts updates
- New endpoint: GET /v1/households/:householdId/display-tablets/:tabletId/config-updates
- SSE heartbeat every 30 seconds to detect dead connections
- Auto cleanup of disconnected tablets

How it works:
1. Tablet connects to /config-updates endpoint with tablet auth
2. Connection stays open (SSE stream)
3. When user updates config via PUT, backend notifies connected tablet
4. Tablet receives event and immediately fetches fresh config
5. Display refreshes instantly without user intervention

Security:
- Only tablets can subscribe to config updates (no user access)
- Tablets can only subscribe to their own updates (validated by tabletId + householdId)
- SSE endpoint uses custom preHandler for tablet-only auth

Benefits:
- Instant config updates (no polling needed)
- Better UX: changes appear immediately on tablets
- Lower bandwidth: no constant polling
- Scalable: SSE is lightweight and efficient
